-- Chinese 4-Year-Old Kidnapped, Killed in Second Shanghai Case, Daily Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-13T00:12:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-13/chinese-4-year-old-kidnapped-killed-in-second-shanghai-case-daily-says.html
A four-year-old Chinese girl was
kidnapped and killed in Shanghai, the second kidnapping-murder
case in the city in the past month, Shanghai Daily reported,
citing unidentified police officers.  The girl, surnamed Sun, was found dead in a creek near her
residence in Baoshan district Dec. 10 and a 16-year-old suspect,
surnamed Guo, was captured by the police on the same day, the
report said.  A different four-year-old girl was killed after being
kidnapped by two men and a juvenile in suburban Songjiang
district on Nov. 20, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 swong139@bloomberg.net  